---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout
  title="PPC Toolbench – Free Google Ads & Marketing Tools"
  description="Practical tools for Google Ads, campaign tracking, and ad copy validation. No sign-up required."
  currentPath="/"
>
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>Free Tools for Google Ads & Marketing Tracking</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Practical, no-nonsense tools for Google Ads, campaign tracking and ad copy validation.
      Built for marketers who want clean workflows, consistent naming, and faster execution.
    </p>

    <div class="hero-actions">
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/utm-builder">Open UTM Builder</a>
      <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="#tools">View all tools</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="tools">
    <h2>Tools</h2>

    <div class="tool-grid">
      <article class="card">
        <div class="status">Live now</div>
        <h3>Google Ads & Affiliate UTM Builder</h3>
        <p>
          Build clean, GA4-friendly campaign URLs for Google Ads, affiliates,
          email, and social traffic.
        </p>
        <ul class="small-list">
          <li>Source and medium defaults</li>
          <li>Clean parameter output</li>
          <li>Copy-ready full URL</li>
        </ul>
        <p><a href="/utm-builder">Open tool →</a></p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <div class="status">Coming next</div>
        <h3>Google Ads Character Counter</h3>
        <p>
          Check headline and description length for responsive search ads
          with simple visual limits.
        </p>
        <ul class="small-list">
          <li>30-character headline checks</li>
          <li>90-character description checks</li>
          <li>Fast drafting workflow</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Launching soon.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <div class="status">Planned</div>
        <h3>Google Ads Copy Draft Tool</h3>
        <p>
          Generate draft ad copy ideas for inspiration, then validate them
          against standard Google Ads length limits.
        </p>
        <ul class="small-list">
          <li>Draft headlines and descriptions</li>
          <li>Region-aware output styles</li>
          <li>Human review recommended</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Planned for the next release.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="info-grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h2>Why PPC Toolbench exists</h2>
        <p>
          Many campaign tools are either too bloated, too generic, or built for large teams.
          PPC Toolbench focuses on small, practical utilities that help marketers execute faster
          without unnecessary complexity.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our goal is simple: build tools that are easy to use, quick to access, and genuinely useful
          in everyday campaign work.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>What you can expect</h2>
        <ul class="small-list">
          <li>No sign-up required for core tools</li>
          <li>Simple interfaces with practical defaults</li>
          <li>Tools designed for real campaign workflows</li>
          <li>Clear documentation and transparent policies</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    padding: 22px 0 10px;
  }

  .hero-actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: 12px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .btn {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 12px 16px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    background: var(--primary);
    color: white;
  }

  .btn-primary:hover {
    background: var(--primary-hover);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .btn-secondary {
    background: #ede9fe;
    color: #4c1d95;
  }

  .btn-secondary:hover {
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .tool-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 18px;
  }

  .card h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
  }

  .card p {
    color: #4b5563;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }

  .status {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #4c1d95;
    background: #f3e8ff;
    padding: 6px 10px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .small-list {
    padding-left: 18px;
    color: #374151;
  }

  .info-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.1fr 0.9fr;
    gap: 18px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .tool-grid,
    .info-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>